            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1597159471438-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1597159471438-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the veg is cooking, add your <strong>bulgur wheat</strong> and<strong> diced apricots </strong>to a pot with plenty of<strong> boiled water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 7-9 min or until tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain and return to the pot</p><p>Meanwhile, heat a large, dry, wide based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) over a medium-high heat</p>",
