            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken is cooked, transfer it to a clean board and return the pan and any <strong>remaining juices</strong> to a low heat</p><p>Add your <strong>harissa paste </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> [2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> to the pan and mix it all together</p><p>Squeeze in the<strong> </strong>juice of <strong>half</strong> your <strong>lemon[s] </strong>and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>– this is your <strong>warm harissa dressing</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining lemon </strong>into wedges</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
